Senate Resolution 441
By: Senators Halpern of the 39th, Jones II of the 22nd, Jackson of the 41st, Mallow of the
2nd, Orrock of the 36th and others
A RESOLUTION
1 Urging action to attract displaced federal workers to Georgia and to encourage federal
2 investment in the state; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) has been headquartered
4 in Atlanta since 1946, contributing to Georgia's role as a hub for public health and federal
5 operations; and
6 WHEREAS, the presence of the CDC, along with various other federal offices in Georgia,
7 has led to a highly skilled federal workforce within the state; and
8 WHEREAS, shifts in federal employment policies have resulted in changes to workforce
9 distribution and agency operations across the country; and
10 WHEREAS, some federal agencies are exploring opportunities to relocate or establish offices
11 in different regions; and
12 WHEREAS, Atlanta, as the capital of Georgia and a major economic and cultural center of
13 the South, is well-positioned to serve as a strategic location for federal investment and
14 workforce expansion; and
