15 WHEREAS, Georgia seeks to strengthen its role as a national leader in innovation, economic
16 development, and workforce growth; and
17 WHEREAS, attracting skilled federal employees to Georgia would benefit the state's
18 workforce and economy while providing new opportunities for those affected by federal
19 employment changes.
20 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
21 urge all state departments, agencies, boards, and other instrumentalities to explore strategies
22 to attract displaced federal employees to Georgia's workforce.
23 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of this body encourage legislative action
24 to support and incentivize employment opportunities for displaced federal workers in both
25 public and private sectors within the state.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
27 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the Governor, heads
28 of state departments and agencies, and the public.
